opencc (1.4.0-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Recreate the Debian packaging flow on top of the existing
    packaging/debian patch mirror, rebased for the 1.4.0 release and
    validated against a clean checkout of upstream BYVoid/OpenCC:
    - Rebase 0003 (no remote images in README.md), 0004 (Use
      system-installed googletest instead of bundled version for Debian
      builds), 0005 (disable CMake build in setup.py), and 0009
      (setup.py handles the python binding directly) — the complete set
      packaging/debian/patches already tracked — so all four apply
      cleanly with `patch -p1 --fuzz=0` against upstream 1.4.0 sources.
    - Split the binary packages the way Debian's existing opencc source
      package already does (opencc, libopencc<soversion>, libopencc-dev,
      libopencc-data, libopencc-doc), updated for the current
      OPENCC_ABI_VERSION (1.4) SOVERSION, plus a new opencc-jieba binary
      package for the Jieba segmentation plugin, which Debian does not
      currently package. See packaging/debian/SPLIT_PROPOSAL.md.
    - Build against system libmarisa, rapidjson, libtclap, and
      googletest via the upstream USE_SYSTEM_* CMake options instead of
      the vendored deps/ copies.
    - Validated with `dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc -b` against upstream
      `master`: all six binary packages build, `dh_missing
      --fail-missing` finds nothing unclaimed, `ctest` passes 19/19, and
      `lintian --pedantic` reports no errors.

 -- Frank Lin <github@linshuang.info>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 02:12:00 +0000
